                  <persName id="t18280911-314-person1703">
                  HENRY 
                  CHURCHILL
               <interp inst="t18280911-314-person1703" type="surname" value="CHURCHILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-314-person1703" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-314-person1703" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. James Drew, a <rs id="t18280911-314-viclabel1612" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-314-victim1702 t18280911-314-viclabel1612"></join>, of Clark's-place, Islington. On the 22d of August, about four o'clock, a person told me some things had been taken; I went out, and saw the prisoner about forty yards off, tying up the trousers - he saw me, turned into another street, and threw down the trousers; I pursued, took him, and took up the trousers - I have seen his master, who will employ him still.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-314-person1704">
                  JAMES 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-314-person1704" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
